-- Saudi Shura Council Asks to Oversee Aramco Income, Riyadh Says
-- B y   W a e l   M a h d i
-- 2012-01-30T08:09:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/saudi-shura-council-asks-to-oversee-aramco-income-riyadh-says.html
Saudi Arabia ’s consultative body,
the  Shura Council , voted yesterday seek the right to oversee and
review the income and activities of Saudi Arabian Oil Co., al-
Riyadh newspaper  said , citing members of the council.  The council will submit a proposal next week to King
Abdullah to oblige the state-owned company known as Saudi Aramco
to prepare an annual report that can be submitted to the council
for review like other state-owned companies, the newspaper
added. Saudi Aramco currently publishes an annual review that
doesn’t show its income.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Wael Mahdi in Khobar, Saudi Arabia at 
 wmahdi@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Stephen Voss  on   sev@bloomberg.net . 